{
  "lesson": "WC-12-04",
  "audioMaster": "training/module12-settings/WC-12-04-full-narration-v1.0.mp3",
  "audioDurationS": 197.486,
  "method": "silencedetect -32dB/0.28s within known block windows; proportional fallback",
  "phrases": [
    {
      "block": "s01",
      "id": "p01",
      "text": "This is where the money rules live.",
      "startS": 0,
      "endS": 1.644,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s01",
      "id": "p02",
      "text": "Open Settings, then the Payments and Finance group.",
      "startS": 2.378,
      "endS": 5.002,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s01",
      "id": "p03",
      "text": "Nine pages, one list.",
      "startS": 5.413,
      "endS": 7.083,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s01",
      "id": "p04",
      "text": "Between them they decide how a payment is taken, how a price gets adjusted,",
      "startS": 7.423,
      "endS": 9.952,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s01",
      "id": "p05",
      "text": "how tax is set, and how a sale lands in accounting.",
      "startS": 10.198,
      "endS": 14.848,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s01",
      "id": "p06",
      "text": "Learn to spot them, because most billing questions end on one of these.",
      "startS": 15.241,
      "endS": 18.93,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s02",
      "id": "p07",
      "text": "Start at Payment Types.",
      "startS": 19.36,
      "endS": 20.892,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s02",
      "id": "p08",
      "text": "This is your tender list, the payment methods the register accepts.",
      "startS": 21.453,
      "endS": 22.979,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s02",
      "id": "p09",
      "text": "Three flags do the real work.",
      "startS": 23.3,
      "endS": 25.234,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s02",
      "id": "p10",
      "text": "Locked marks the system types you can't delete.",
      "startS": 25.707,
      "endS": 27.252,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s02",
      "id": "p11",
      "text": "Require Reference forces a number at the register.",
      "startS": 27.588,
      "endS": 30.07,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s02",
      "id": "p12",
      "text": "And Show as Bank Drop decides what counts toward the drawer drop.",
      "startS": 30.367,
      "endS": 36.702,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s03",
      "id": "p13",
      "text": "Now Discounts.",
      "startS": 37.2,
      "endS": 38.512,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s03",
      "id": "p14",
      "text": "The panels up top read the file at a glance:",
      "startS": 39.17,
      "endS": 42.938,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s03",
      "id": "p15",
      "text": "how many are active, how they split between dollars off and percent off.",
      "startS": 43.19,
      "endS": 45.7,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s03",
      "id": "p16",
      "text": "But the row that answers questions is Amount, next to Discount Type.",
      "startS": 46.218,
      "endS": 50.192,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s03",
      "id": "p17",
      "text": "That pair tells you fast whether a discount takes three dollars off or ten percent.",
      "startS": 50.617,
      "endS": 55.599,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s04",
      "id": "p18",
      "text": "Open one discount and it behaves like a service.",
      "startS": 56,
      "endS": 58.772,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s04",
      "id": "p19",
      "text": "A detail view, an Active Locations tab, the sites where it's live,",
      "startS": 59.199,
      "endS": 60.144,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s04",
      "id": "p20",
      "text": "and per-location overrides underneath.",
      "startS": 60.358,
      "endS": 63.395,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s04",
      "id": "p21",
      "text": "That's how one discount is three dollars off at one wash and two at another.",
      "startS": 63.605,
      "endS": 66.171,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s04",
      "id": "p22",
      "text": "We couldn't pull this exact screen from today's capture,",
      "startS": 66.406,
      "endS": 70.534,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s04",
      "id": "p23",
      "text": "so lean on the Services lesson as your reference until we grab it live.",
      "startS": 71.14,
      "endS": 78.03,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s04",
      "id": "p24",
      "text": "Look, don't save.",
      "startS": 78.64,
      "endS": 79.951,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s05",
      "id": "p25",
      "text": "Discount Types is the short list behind that column.",
      "startS": 80.8,
      "endS": 84.18,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s05",
      "id": "p26",
      "text": "Four categories, nothing more.",
      "startS": 85.073,
      "endS": 86.899,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s05",
      "id": "p27",
      "text": "Whatever shows under Discount Type on the list you just saw is filed from here.",
      "startS": 87.543,
      "endS": 91.913,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s06",
      "id": "p28",
      "text": "Surcharges are the mirror of a discount.",
      "startS": 92.4,
      "endS": 94.835,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s06",
      "id": "p29",
      "text": "Same idea, opposite sign.",
      "startS": 95.251,
      "endS": 96.1,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s06",
      "id": "p30",
      "text": "An added fee, with an amount, a code, and a taxable flag",
      "startS": 96.312,
      "endS": 97.168,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s06",
      "id": "p31",
      "text": "that decides whether tax rides on top of the fee.",
      "startS": 97.777,
      "endS": 104.16,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s07",
      "id": "p32",
      "text": "Surcharge Types carries one flag worth knowing.",
      "startS": 104.56,
      "endS": 107.318,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s07",
      "id": "p33",
      "text": "Disallow Discounts.",
      "startS": 107.822,
      "endS": 109.171,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s07",
      "id": "p34",
      "text": "Switch it on, and a discount can't stack on a ticket that already has this surcharge.",
      "startS": 109.678,
      "endS": 114.195,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s07",
      "id": "p35",
      "text": "That single control settles a lot of pricing arguments.",
      "startS": 114.597,
      "endS": 117.748,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s08",
      "id": "p36",
      "text": "Payout Percentage is a band table.",
      "startS": 118.258,
      "endS": 120.36,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s08",
      "id": "p37",
      "text": "Each row is a range, a start and an end, with a percentage inside it.",
      "startS": 120.836,
      "endS": 125.143,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s08",
      "id": "p38",
      "text": "A value drops into whichever band it lands in.",
      "startS": 125.606,
      "endS": 128.149,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s08",
      "id": "p39",
      "text": "Tiered, not flat.",
      "startS": 128.441,
      "endS": 129.787,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s09",
      "id": "p40",
      "text": "Tax Rates feeds the rest of the platform.",
      "startS": 130.309,
      "endS": 132.619,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s09",
      "id": "p41",
      "text": "Every rate here is what a service reaches for in its two tax slots.",
      "startS": 132.957,
      "endS": 136.926,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s09",
      "id": "p42",
      "text": "So when a wash rings up the wrong tax, don't start at the service.",
      "startS": 137.294,
      "endS": 141.76,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s09",
      "id": "p43",
      "text": "Start here, and check which rate is the default.",
      "startS": 142.053,
      "endS": 143.991,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s10",
      "id": "p44",
      "text": "Down to accounting.",
      "startS": 144.48,
      "endS": 145.615,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s10",
      "id": "p45",
      "text": "General Ledger Codes.",
      "startS": 145.615,
      "endS": 146.75,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s10",
      "id": "p46",
      "text": "One small catch worth remembering:",
      "startS": 146.75,
      "endS": 149.275,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s10",
      "id": "p47",
      "text": "the sidebar says General Ledger Codes, the page header says G-L Codes.",
      "startS": 149.275,
      "endS": 154.463,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s10",
      "id": "p48",
      "text": "Same page.",
      "startS": 154.463,
      "endS": 155.22,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s10",
      "id": "p49",
      "text": "These codes are what your exports post against,",
      "startS": 155.22,
      "endS": 158.995,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s10",
      "id": "p50",
      "text": "and a wrong one here is a classic month-end headache.",
      "startS": 158.995,
      "endS": 162.778,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s11",
      "id": "p51",
      "text": "G-L Account Codes is the partner list.",
      "startS": 163.28,
      "endS": 165.801,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s11",
      "id": "p52",
      "text": "Same three columns, same shape.",
      "startS": 166.247,
      "endS": 168.26,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s11",
      "id": "p53",
      "text": "Here's the split: G-L Codes name the ledger lines,",
      "startS": 168.655,
      "endS": 169.452,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s11",
      "id": "p54",
      "text": "and G-L Account Codes tie them to accounts for the export.",
      "startS": 169.943,
      "endS": 175.202,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s11",
      "id": "p55",
      "text": "The two work as a pair.",
      "startS": 175.522,
      "endS": 176.759,
      "timing": "silence"
    },
    {
      "block": "s12",
      "id": "p56",
      "text": "That's the whole group.",
      "startS": 177.2,
      "endS": 178.891,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s12",
      "id": "p57",
      "text": "Nine pages, one sidebar.",
      "startS": 178.891,
      "endS": 180.226,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s12",
      "id": "p58",
      "text": "Tender in Payment Types.",
      "startS": 180.226,
      "endS": 182.831,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s12",
      "id": "p59",
      "text": "Price changes in Discounts and Surcharges.",
      "startS": 182.831,
      "endS": 185.222,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s12",
      "id": "p60",
      "text": "Tiered payouts, tax, and the two ledger lists.",
      "startS": 185.222,
      "endS": 188.162,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s12",
      "id": "p61",
      "text": "When a billing question comes in, you already know which page owns the answer.",
      "startS": 188.162,
      "endS": 194.032,
      "timing": "proportional"
    },
    {
      "block": "s12",
      "id": "p62",
      "text": "And you got there without touching a single setting.",
      "startS": 194.032,
      "endS": 197.036,
      "timing": "proportional"
    }
  ]
}